cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM. 

The paper focuses on the problem of multi-domain image generation, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new model based on conditional GANs, which is a popular deep learning technique for image generation, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The regularizers introduced in the proposed model are designed to guide the model to learn the corresponding semantics of different domains, which involves a certain level of artificial intelligence, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category. The paper also evaluates the proposed model on several tasks, including the generation of edges and photos, the generation of faces with different attributes, etc., which may fall under the sub-categories of cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
